WEBVTT

00:05.089 --> 00:06.090
[upbeat music playing]

00:06.174 --> 00:08.718
[Maria] <i>Single, stylish, now.</i>

00:09.177 --> 00:11.763
<i>A lady's got to be ready</i>
<i>for when it happens.</i>

00:11.846 --> 00:15.558
<i>And right now, it's happening.</i>

00:15.642 --> 00:16.809
<i>It's my life.</i>

00:16.893 --> 00:20.480
<i>And I'll do whatever it takes</i>
<i>to get that sassafras feeling.</i>

00:20.563 --> 00:21.648
Sassafras.

00:23.483 --> 00:24.525
[Maria] Thank you.

00:25.985 --> 00:27.862
I'm a silly goose-snake.

00:29.113 --> 00:30.907
Ooh! [laughing]

00:31.991 --> 00:33.409
<i>I feel French.</i>

00:33.493 --> 00:36.663
<i>Ooh, flowers for me?</i>
<i>No, thanks.</i>

00:38.498 --> 00:40.208
[bicycle chain clicking]

00:41.042 --> 00:44.963
<i>Sometimes you just have to take a ride</i>
<i>when life wants you to.</i>

00:45.880 --> 00:47.298
-Bye!
-[bike bell ringing]

00:47.382 --> 00:49.467
<i>Who knows what romance it will bring?</i>

00:49.550 --> 00:52.262
It's not what's in your head,
it's what's on it.

00:52.345 --> 00:53.846
[slurping]

00:53.972 --> 00:55.515
[tire screeches]

00:57.600 --> 00:59.352
<i>Hair that's so shiny and full...</i>

01:00.103 --> 01:02.230
Can you blame them for looking?

01:02.313 --> 01:04.315
<i>No time to pay.</i> [giggling]

01:05.483 --> 01:07.860
<i>I love being a woman.</i>

01:07.944 --> 01:09.320
<i>Can a man do this?</i>

01:12.198 --> 01:13.366
[giggling]

01:13.449 --> 01:15.368
First lady on the moon?

01:19.080 --> 01:21.583
Thanks to Latrisse DuVois
Hair Care Products,

01:21.666 --> 01:23.001
by Gary.

01:24.127 --> 01:25.920
I just had my tubes tied.

01:26.004 --> 01:28.756
At my age, it's not safe to have children.

01:28.840 --> 01:30.091
[tires squealing]

01:30.258 --> 01:32.260
Get out of the way, you gypsies!

01:36.055 --> 01:36.931
[bell chiming]

01:37.515 --> 01:39.600
<i>Because when you feel this good...</i>

01:39.684 --> 01:42.437
Ain't no man gonna tell me
I ain't a woman.

01:42.520 --> 01:44.480
[woman] <i>Uh, Maria.</i>

01:44.564 --> 01:46.691
Hey, Maria. What are you doing?

01:48.276 --> 01:49.986
Uh, hair commercial?

01:50.069 --> 01:52.447
[woman] No. This is not a hair ad.

01:52.530 --> 01:53.448
It's the show.

01:53.531 --> 01:54.741
It's your show.

01:55.408 --> 01:57.994
-Let's get you to the van, okay?
-My show?

01:58.828 --> 01:59.912
I have a show?

02:01.122 --> 02:05.126
I'm a 45-year-old woman,
who's clearly sun-damaged.

02:05.209 --> 02:08.170
My skin's getting softer,
yet my bones are jutting out,

02:08.253 --> 02:10.840
so I'm half soft, half sharp.

02:10.923 --> 02:12.550
And I have a show!

02:12.634 --> 02:15.637
What a great late-in-life opportunity!
[chuckling]

02:15.720 --> 02:16.846
[woman] Maria!

02:17.805 --> 02:19.057
Wrong van!

02:19.140 --> 02:20.475
Oh.
[door slamming]

02:20.558 --> 02:22.101
Stranger danger.

02:22.185 --> 02:24.103
I have my own sho--

02:25.104 --> 02:27.065
[theme music playing]

02:27.148 --> 02:28.232
[Maria] <i> Pow!</i>

02:28.316 --> 02:29.359
<i>Kick it!</i>

02:29.901 --> 02:30.902
[Maria laughing]

02:32.695 --> 02:34.197
[Maria trills]

02:34.280 --> 02:35.365
[Maria screaming]

02:36.449 --> 02:38.493
<i>Have you ever been to Detroit?</i>

02:40.620 --> 02:42.038
[on phone]
<i>It's Maria Bamford</i>

02:42.121 --> 02:43.331
<i>to see Bruce Ben-Bacharach.</i>

02:43.414 --> 02:44.957
<i>He's my manager.</i>

02:45.041 --> 02:47.668
-Bruce?
-[Bruce] Ah!

02:47.752 --> 02:48.669
-How are you?
-Good!

02:48.753 --> 02:51.214
I'm thrilled to see you.
You look lovely.

02:51.297 --> 02:52.965
Please come into my office.

02:53.049 --> 02:55.134
-Hey!
-The prodigal son returns.

02:55.218 --> 02:57.762
Six long months and now you're back.

02:57.845 --> 03:00.598
How do you feel?
Refreshed? Revitalized? Renewed?

03:00.681 --> 03:02.975
Yes, I do... I feel...

03:03.059 --> 03:07.146
I feel very good, a little tired
because of the heavy meds.

03:07.230 --> 03:09.857
But, I'm also back on carbs.

03:09.941 --> 03:13.236
I'm eating pancakes almost all day.

03:13.319 --> 03:16.948
The entire entertainment industry
has been eagerly awaiting

03:17.031 --> 03:18.658
-your glorious return.
-[sighs]

03:18.741 --> 03:20.701
I've made some big changes, too.

03:21.577 --> 03:23.579
Big Hollywood power desk.

03:23.663 --> 03:25.373
-Solid glass. That's not all.
-Oh.

03:25.456 --> 03:26.749
Kerplunk.

03:26.833 --> 03:29.502
Sexy Hollywood power boots.

03:29.585 --> 03:32.296
Move over, Carrie Bradshaw.
From <i>Sex and the City</i>.

03:32.380 --> 03:34.090
I'd like to get you booked on that.

03:34.173 --> 03:35.466
-Is it still on?
-[clunking]

03:35.550 --> 03:37.760
[Bruce] God damn it.
Sexy power boots!

03:38.094 --> 03:41.806
Now that you're back,
tell me exactly what you want to do.

03:41.889 --> 03:45.309
-Right.
-TV show, movie, world comedy tour...

03:45.393 --> 03:47.186
I'm gonna take a real shot at it.

03:47.270 --> 03:49.105
-Yeah.
-Chantrelle!

03:49.188 --> 03:52.150
Get me the hidden big opportunities list,
would you?

03:52.233 --> 03:55.778
Okay, I would like to do less, not more.

03:55.862 --> 03:59.115
That's the thing.
Could it be less ambitious?

03:59.198 --> 04:01.909
Or maybe not ambitious anymore.

04:01.993 --> 04:03.286
Less ambitious?

04:03.870 --> 04:05.288
No work for Maria.

04:05.371 --> 04:08.916
I mean, I want to work a little,
but just smaller things.

04:09.000 --> 04:10.460
Less pressure. I mean...

04:10.543 --> 04:12.044
Stand-up at a book store,

04:12.128 --> 04:16.841
alone in my living room
or in a vintage eyeglass shop, or--

04:16.923 --> 04:19.677
Sweetheart, are you pulling back
because of me?

04:19.761 --> 04:23.598
I can reel in that big fish.
I can land the monster shark.

04:23.681 --> 04:25.516
Believe me, you've seen the desk.

04:25.600 --> 04:27.685
No. This is not about you at all.

04:27.769 --> 04:30.021
I'm trying to get some balance in my life.

04:30.104 --> 04:33.065
I know I've done some things I regret

04:33.149 --> 04:35.234
and I made some enemies, I'm sure,

04:35.318 --> 04:39.405
-from some of my behavior and I'd--
-[Chantrelle] Mark "Sugar Ray" McGrath?

04:39.489 --> 04:40.531
[Maria] Okay. What?

04:40.615 --> 04:42.658
-The singer?
-Don't listen to her.

04:42.742 --> 04:44.243
-[thudding]
-[inhaling sharply]

04:46.496 --> 04:48.790
[glass crackling]

04:50.166 --> 04:52.668
-I bet they can buff that out.
-I'm sure.

04:52.752 --> 04:53.920
You know what it is?

04:54.003 --> 04:56.881
I just really wanna reconnect
with my community.

04:56.964 --> 04:59.634
I don't even know who my neighbors are.

04:59.717 --> 05:03.387
Forgive my distraction. This is
a $37,000 handblown Murano glass desk.

05:03.471 --> 05:04.305
Oh, my God.

05:04.388 --> 05:06.390
So understandably I'm irked with myself.

05:06.474 --> 05:09.977
Yes, neighbors.
A serendipitous meeting on a park bench.

05:10.061 --> 05:11.103
"How do you do, sir?"

05:11.187 --> 05:13.523
"I'm fine, thank you."
"Is that your dog, sir?"

05:13.606 --> 05:14.857
That's it.

05:14.941 --> 05:17.944
Human interaction. Indeed.
I'm gonna make some calls.

05:18.027 --> 05:19.529
I love it. I love it.

05:19.612 --> 05:21.572
A neighborhood park bench.

05:21.656 --> 05:23.783
That's exactly
what was on my vision board.

05:24.283 --> 05:25.785
<i>When I was in the psych ward,</i>

05:25.868 --> 05:28.287
<i>I kept cutting out benches </i>
<i>for my vision board.</i>

05:28.371 --> 05:30.790
<i>-I didn't know why. And now I know:</i>
-[inaudible]

05:30.873 --> 05:32.583
<i>It was to manifest community!</i>

05:32.667 --> 05:34.293
Bruce, you did it!

05:34.377 --> 05:36.587
I'm not sure what you're talking about,

05:36.671 --> 05:39.048
but you're happy with me.
That's what matters.

05:39.131 --> 05:40.591
-Yes.
-Solutions everywhere.

05:40.675 --> 05:42.927
By the way,
I'm gonna call these people.

05:43.010 --> 05:45.596
I'm gonna say they delivered
the desk that way

05:45.680 --> 05:47.223
and how dare you, sir!

05:47.306 --> 05:50.017
Really, why should I pay
for the buffing? [chuckling]

05:50.101 --> 05:52.353
[glass shattering]

05:53.020 --> 05:55.856
Well... That's it.

05:55.940 --> 05:57.775
I put my foot through my nest egg.

05:57.858 --> 05:59.151
[Maria] Oh!
[dial tone]

06:00.278 --> 06:01.320
[Maria] <i>The bench arrived.</i>

06:01.404 --> 06:04.699
<i>I invited my best friend, Dagmar,</i>
<i>and her worst friend,</i>

06:04.782 --> 06:06.701
<i>Larissa, also my best friend.</i>

06:06.784 --> 06:08.744
-Hey, dipshit.
-Hey!

06:08.828 --> 06:12.623
-What's with the bench?
-Hey. Well, it is to connect

06:12.707 --> 06:13.916
and create community.

06:14.000 --> 06:15.960
How fun.

06:16.043 --> 06:19.255
Isn't this great?
It's all coming together.

06:19.338 --> 06:21.048
Why? Because you have a bench?

06:21.132 --> 06:23.551
It's not just my bench,
it's your bench, Dagmar.

06:23.634 --> 06:24.760
It's your bench, Larissa.

06:24.844 --> 06:27.930
-Thank you.
-It's your bench, sir!

06:28.014 --> 06:29.515
Come have a seat.

06:29.599 --> 06:30.850
[grunts]

06:30.933 --> 06:32.810
That's it.
I'm gonna rip you in half.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.687
That guy needs a bench for sure.

06:34.770 --> 06:37.315
[Dagmar] Why don't you come back?
You kidding me?

06:37.398 --> 06:39.525
Know what?
I'm gonna make a note of this guy

06:39.609 --> 06:40.985
in my notebook.

06:41.068 --> 06:45.323
Oh, I get it. This bench is a way
for you to access romance.

06:45.406 --> 06:46.657
-No.
-[Larissa] Yes.

06:46.741 --> 06:49.744
-It's like a fuck bench? I love that.
-No, no!

06:49.827 --> 06:53.497
That's the way to build community.
Sit here all night, suck Ds,

06:53.581 --> 06:55.374
knock out your teeth,
have a good time.

06:55.458 --> 06:58.794
[Larissa] Maybe it's time
to get back out there? S some Ds.

06:58.878 --> 07:00.880
It's about learning people's names.

07:00.963 --> 07:03.299
The more names you learn,
the happier you are.

07:03.382 --> 07:05.092
-[Larissa] I didn't know that.

07:05.176 --> 07:06.469
You're a bad friend.

07:06.552 --> 07:08.512
I am a wonderful friend.

07:08.596 --> 07:09.972
-Oh, really?
-Mhmm.

07:10.056 --> 07:12.391
You didn't visit Maria
in her time of need.

07:12.475 --> 07:14.393
We've already talked about this.

07:14.477 --> 07:16.312
I didn't need to be visited. Besides,

07:16.395 --> 07:18.648
-I'm sure you were busy, Larissa.
-I wasn't.

07:18.731 --> 07:20.858
-Okay.
-I wasn't busy at all.

07:20.942 --> 07:22.902
I didn't come because I'm an empath.

07:22.985 --> 07:25.947
When people are experiencing
negative emotion,

07:26.030 --> 07:28.074
it sticks to me hardcore.

07:28.157 --> 07:30.076
-Yeah.
-[Larissa] So, I guess...

07:30.159 --> 07:33.120
It's like I cared too much to show up.

07:33.204 --> 07:34.914
[Dagmar] You're a bad friend.

07:34.997 --> 07:39.126
Look at this! The bench has got us
communicating as a group.

07:39.210 --> 07:40.920
Let's go meet the neighbors!

07:41.003 --> 07:42.505
Okay.

07:42.588 --> 07:44.256
Oh, God. I'm terrified.

07:46.050 --> 07:47.468
[knocking]

07:49.261 --> 07:50.262
Hi.

07:50.346 --> 07:54.183
I'm Maria...
and your name is, please, sir?

07:55.393 --> 07:57.770
-Oscar.
-Hi, Oscar.

07:57.853 --> 08:01.273
I am your neighbor
and these are my friends...

08:02.024 --> 08:04.402
I wanted to let you know
I put in a bench

08:04.485 --> 08:06.529
that I wanted you to come over and enjoy.

08:06.612 --> 08:07.655
Go fuck yourself.

08:07.738 --> 08:08.948
Okay--

08:12.868 --> 08:14.328
Hi! I'm Maria. I'm from...

08:14.412 --> 08:16.497
I live across the street and...

08:16.580 --> 08:18.249
Just... gonna put in a bench.

08:18.332 --> 08:19.834
I think it's helpful for--

08:19.917 --> 08:21.669
Okay, all right. That's good.

08:21.752 --> 08:25.006
And I just wanna invite you
and your family or-- Okay.

08:25.089 --> 08:29.385
[Dagmar] We are loving, open people!
Don't shut the fucking door in my face!

08:29.468 --> 08:31.262
[Maria] No? Okay.

08:31.345 --> 08:32.388
She hates you.

08:32.471 --> 08:34.306
[Dagmar] I'll kick her ass!

08:36.392 --> 08:38.309
Why don't you put that in a fun binder?

08:38.394 --> 08:41.480
I'm not very organized
and don't have the resources--

08:41.563 --> 08:43.607
Maria, I just had a Larissa thought.

08:43.691 --> 08:44.734
-Okay.
-Okay?

08:44.817 --> 08:46.736
Let me be your assistant.

08:47.653 --> 08:50.072
That would make me feel really useful.

08:50.156 --> 08:51.449
The only way to be sure

08:51.532 --> 08:53.993
that I'll be there for you
is if you pay me.

08:54.076 --> 08:56.162
-Okay.
-I'm gonna need $35 an hour.

08:56.245 --> 08:58.414
The music in the house
has to be my choice.

08:58.497 --> 08:59.832
I need Wednesdays off.

08:59.915 --> 09:01.792
It's religious.
You're not allowed to ask.

09:01.876 --> 09:04.211
Six weeks off in summer,
like the Italians.

09:04.795 --> 09:05.671
You know what?

09:06.714 --> 09:09.592
I do need help.
And it's okay to admit that.

09:10.843 --> 09:13.137
I accept with love and gratitude.
You're hired.

09:13.220 --> 09:14.096
Great!

09:14.180 --> 09:16.599
I have an appointment.
I'll be 4 hours late.

09:16.682 --> 09:18.726
Okay, it's all coming together.

09:18.809 --> 09:22.063
Yeah, even my... bench
which is now covered in garbage.

09:22.188 --> 09:23.689
-Okay. All right.
-Oh, no.

09:24.648 --> 09:26.859
It's become a bit of a wildlife preserve.

09:26.942 --> 09:28.903
-[siren wails]
-Evening, ladies.

09:28.986 --> 09:31.030
-Hi, Officer.
-You can't just...

09:31.113 --> 09:33.657
dump your furniture and garbage out here.

09:33.741 --> 09:35.159
Oh, no, it's not garbage.

09:35.242 --> 09:38.746
It's a neighborhood bench.
It's for the community.

09:38.829 --> 09:41.957
Do you have a permit
for the community bench?

09:42.041 --> 09:45.544
-Oh, no. Is that required?
-It is.

09:45.628 --> 09:48.631
If you don't have one,
you're gonna have to go down

09:48.714 --> 09:50.549
to City Hall and get one.

09:50.633 --> 09:52.760
-Or I can write you a 4950.
-[Maria groans]

09:52.843 --> 09:54.678
I don't wanna write you a 4950.

09:54.762 --> 09:58.224
I can't do it right now.
I have to get ready for a stand-up gig.

09:58.307 --> 10:00.768
-Oh, invite him.
-[Maria] Maybe...

10:00.851 --> 10:02.853
What a helmet.
That's a good shaped head,

10:02.937 --> 10:04.688
if you know what I mean.

10:04.772 --> 10:08.484
Would you wanna come to a comedy show?

10:08.567 --> 10:10.194
They're so wonderful.

10:11.487 --> 10:14.156
[stammering] Oh, God.

10:14.240 --> 10:15.991
Maria, I'm sorry. Come here.

10:16.075 --> 10:18.536
You're gonna put stand-up in your show?

10:18.619 --> 10:20.788
-[man] Cut!
-Yeah. Is that bad?

10:20.871 --> 10:22.498
It's... Yeah, it's bad.

10:22.581 --> 10:24.834
It's just been done so many times.

10:24.917 --> 10:27.837
You know, you got Louie,
Seinfeld, Chappelle,

10:27.920 --> 10:29.296
Amy Schumer, my two pilots...

10:30.131 --> 10:31.841
-They didn't go.
-I'm so sorry.

10:31.924 --> 10:34.885
We haven't officially met.
Are you the comedy police?

10:34.969 --> 10:37.930
I'm a friend giving friendly advice.

10:38.013 --> 10:40.391
You're an actor.
Just say your lines, monkey.

10:41.308 --> 10:42.768
Give your audience some credit.

10:42.852 --> 10:46.355
They can deal with
form-busting narrative innovations.

10:46.438 --> 10:48.065
-We've all seen <i>Breaking Bad.</i>

10:48.149 --> 10:50.442
All right, well, I haven't.

10:50.526 --> 10:52.862
You gotta see it.
Anna Gunn is amazing in it.

10:52.945 --> 10:55.781
But look, people can deal
with the time jump.

10:55.865 --> 10:59.368
All right? Just don't make it jarring.

10:59.451 --> 11:01.370
If we do, we definitely wouldn't do it

11:01.453 --> 11:03.038
in a way that was jarring.

11:06.500 --> 11:08.169
Here you go.

11:08.252 --> 11:10.796
And don't thank me.
I'm a stranger.

11:12.381 --> 11:14.258
[upbeat music]

11:14.341 --> 11:16.218
-[Maria] Hi.
-Karen Grisham.

11:16.302 --> 11:18.971
-Come here, I'm a hugger.
-Oh, thank you.

11:19.054 --> 11:20.556
Wow.

11:20.639 --> 11:22.558
Congrats, Maria.

11:22.641 --> 11:23.934
-You made the Grish-list.

11:25.102 --> 11:30.566
Maria, I am the most powerful
talent agent in this city or galaxy.

11:30.649 --> 11:33.110
You know why?
Every time I walk into a room,

11:33.193 --> 11:35.487
I know exactly how
I would kill each person.

11:35.571 --> 11:36.780
[waiter] Arnold Palmer?

11:36.864 --> 11:38.866
Elbow to forehead,
golf pencil through heart.

11:40.242 --> 11:42.119
-He meant the drink.
-Oh.

11:42.202 --> 11:44.622
A fucking beverage.
Fuck off, I'm in a meeting.

11:45.289 --> 11:47.124
Look, open-kimono time.

11:47.207 --> 11:48.959
I asked you here 'cause I'm a fan.

11:49.043 --> 11:51.086
-This is a fan lunch, okay?
-Wow.

11:51.170 --> 11:53.130
The world loves you.
I love you.

11:53.213 --> 11:56.675
You are a hilarious...

11:58.010 --> 12:00.596
-Comedian.
-[both laughing]

12:00.679 --> 12:03.057
So, you wanna represent me or...

12:03.140 --> 12:06.477
Are you kidding me?
I would murder that waiter,

12:06.560 --> 12:09.063
snapping his gay neck,
jamming that oyster fork

12:09.146 --> 12:10.940
in both eyes to represent you.

12:11.023 --> 12:13.609
But Karen Grisham's booked.
Sorry. Got a full boat.

12:13.692 --> 12:16.278
-Ah.
-I got so many goddamn clients.

12:16.362 --> 12:17.488
-Yeah.
-And honestly,

12:17.571 --> 12:19.406
I just wanna be your friend, okay?

12:19.490 --> 12:21.825
When paparazzi chase you at
the Trevi Fountain

12:21.909 --> 12:24.536
to get a shot of your rancid snapper,
I got your back.

12:24.620 --> 12:26.622
-That's so nice.
-I swear to God,

12:26.705 --> 12:30.417
I will airlift in one of those
Italian fucking scooter things.

12:30.501 --> 12:33.128
What are they fucking called?
Ves... Uh...

12:33.212 --> 12:34.505
-Ves... uh...
-Vespa.

12:34.588 --> 12:36.632
[both laughing]

12:36.715 --> 12:38.008
Okay, that's good.

12:38.092 --> 12:39.843
-[laughing]
-Oh, come on.

12:39.927 --> 12:41.428
You on a Vespa?

12:41.512 --> 12:43.472
That is my new favorite image.

12:43.555 --> 12:44.807
I swear, that is good.

12:44.890 --> 12:46.100
[both laughing]

12:46.183 --> 12:48.268
-See? We're friends, right?
-Yeah, I know.

12:48.352 --> 12:50.437
You're riding tall on the Vespa.
I'm in...

12:50.521 --> 12:52.147
