26:06.649 --> 26:08.318
They didn't deserve that.

26:08.401 --> 26:10.904
I guess we all fall short
of the glory of God.

26:11.780 --> 26:13.531
Great therapist, though.

26:13.615 --> 26:16.659
Yeah, she's really funny.

26:16.743 --> 26:19.120
[Susan] I hope
they can shrink Maria's brain.

26:19.204 --> 26:21.498
Isn't that funny?

26:21.581 --> 26:24.876
All the fame and fortune
of Hollywood can't save you...

26:24.959 --> 26:27.045
if your brain done broke!

26:27.128 --> 26:28.630
[clock ticking]

26:31.800 --> 26:33.843
And how does that make you feel?

26:36.805 --> 26:38.431
Hungry.

26:40.558 --> 26:42.352
I'll get dinner then.

26:42.435 --> 26:44.020
[chuckles nervously]

26:44.103 --> 26:46.940
This is called truth badminton.

26:47.023 --> 26:51.277
Each player has to express a frustration
whenever you hit the birdie.

26:51.361 --> 26:52.821
All right, begin!

26:52.904 --> 26:54.197
You're weak!

26:54.280 --> 26:56.449
You have interesting bangs.

26:56.533 --> 26:57.784
You're selfish!

26:59.077 --> 27:01.287
You have wonderful teeth!

27:01.371 --> 27:02.664
Say something angry!

27:02.747 --> 27:05.041
That's a cute sweater!

27:05.124 --> 27:06.543
No one likes you!

27:06.626 --> 27:08.878
I do enjoy my time alone!

27:08.962 --> 27:10.547
You don't belong anywhere!

27:10.630 --> 27:15.134
At least my sister didn't give
my ex-husband a blowjob

27:15.218 --> 27:17.554
in front of my two underage Maltese!

27:20.807 --> 27:22.684
I'm so sorry. I'm so...

27:23.726 --> 27:25.061
Oh, God.

27:27.689 --> 27:29.232
They were Shih Tzus.

27:30.733 --> 27:32.569
[breath trembling]

27:32.652 --> 27:33.736
[chainsaw whirring]

27:35.488 --> 27:36.906
[Bruce] And stop. It's perfect.

27:36.990 --> 27:39.951
[Maria] <i>I knew what it was like</i>
<i>to be ostracized by my community.</i>

27:40.034 --> 27:42.495
<i>And I wasn't gonna let that happen again.</i>

27:44.581 --> 27:47.083
Bruce! What are you doing?

27:47.166 --> 27:48.918
[Bruce] Producing!

27:49.002 --> 27:51.504
You know, set dec,
construction, lighting...

27:51.588 --> 27:54.173
Comedy festivals do not
appear out of thin air.

27:54.257 --> 27:57.343
This isn't a comedy festival.
It's a block party.

27:57.427 --> 28:00.555
[Bruce] Caution, my queen.
[Maria] Oh, jeez. Thank you.

28:00.638 --> 28:03.600
Neighbors are turning against me
because of the bench.

28:03.683 --> 28:06.102
[Bruce] Don't worry.
You ain't seen nothing.

28:06.185 --> 28:07.687
Step into my office, okay?

28:09.230 --> 28:10.607
Maria!

28:10.690 --> 28:12.483
That belongs to Mr. Mark McGrath.

28:15.612 --> 28:16.863
[Bruce] <i>I sense agitation.</i>

28:16.946 --> 28:20.658
Look, Bruce, I can't do this.
Open Arms is open carry.

28:20.742 --> 28:22.201
Did you know?

28:22.285 --> 28:25.580
I did not read the fine print
until yesterday afternoon.

28:25.663 --> 28:28.708
At that point, I was beyond chagrin,
so I hid from you.

28:28.791 --> 28:31.419
-Mostly in here.
-I don't know what to do.

28:31.502 --> 28:33.922
If I do do stand-up,
Patton will banish me

28:34.005 --> 28:35.673
from alternative comedy.

28:35.757 --> 28:37.383
But if don't do stand-up,

28:37.467 --> 28:40.428
I let down my community and...

28:40.511 --> 28:41.638
Mark McGrath.

28:41.721 --> 28:43.598
Especially since we sold tickets.

28:44.849 --> 28:48.603
-You charged these people?
-Look, it was a square deal, Maria.

28:48.686 --> 28:50.897
With a wrist band,
they get an orange drink.

28:50.980 --> 28:53.441
People are really going to hate me.

28:53.524 --> 28:56.402
I get it, you're disappointed
in my performance.

28:56.486 --> 28:58.738
-No.
-It's a familiar shade for old Bruce.

28:58.821 --> 29:00.198
-It's fine.
-No, Bruce...

29:00.281 --> 29:03.201
I sunk a tremendous amount
of my own money into this.

29:03.284 --> 29:04.410
-That's all.
-Oh, God.

29:04.494 --> 29:06.037
I'm with you, no matter what.

29:06.120 --> 29:07.247
-Okay.
-Totally!

29:07.330 --> 29:10.583
Because I am now,
and shall ever remain, your chum.

29:10.667 --> 29:12.126
[camera shutter clicking]

29:12.210 --> 29:13.503
[police radio chatter]

29:13.586 --> 29:15.088
I'll give it more thought.

29:15.171 --> 29:17.382
-That's all I'm asking.
-Okay.

29:17.465 --> 29:19.092
[Maria] <i>I felt I owed it to Mark</i>

29:19.175 --> 29:20.385
<i>to go ahead with the party.</i>

29:20.468 --> 29:23.721
<i>I didn't have to do stand-up,</i>
<i>I could tell stories from the heart.</i>

29:23.805 --> 29:25.390
<i>As long as I pulled</i>
<i>the neighborhood together,</i>

29:25.473 --> 29:27.267
<i>it would be a success.</i>

29:27.350 --> 29:29.686
I'd like to introduce you
to a friend of mine,

29:29.811 --> 29:32.313
but instead here's Bruce Ben-Bacharach.

29:32.397 --> 29:34.983
-[scattered applause]
-[man] Orange drink sucks!

29:35.066 --> 29:36.859
[Bruce clearing throat]

29:36.943 --> 29:39.279
What Mark failed to mention is that

29:39.362 --> 29:42.532
VIP wrist bands are good
for only one orange drink.

29:42.615 --> 29:46.369
Please make sure to put all
your business cards into the fish bowl

29:46.452 --> 29:48.663
for the drawing of the dual-action shotgun

29:48.746 --> 29:49.872
from Lil Slaughters.

29:49.956 --> 29:52.542
Lil Slaughters, let's do something
about mental illness.

29:52.625 --> 29:54.252
-Yeah!
-[gunshot]

29:54.335 --> 29:57.505
Now everybody,
please enjoy the hilarious comedy

29:57.588 --> 29:59.841
of the great Maria Bamford!

30:00.717 --> 30:01.801
[all cheering]

30:01.884 --> 30:03.636
Okay, um...

30:04.637 --> 30:08.141
Thank you so much.
Let's not call it comedy,

30:08.224 --> 30:10.351
let's call it neighbor talk.

30:10.435 --> 30:13.438
Oh, Christ. You weren't kidding.

30:13.563 --> 30:15.523
-She's gonna do stand-up.
-[Patton sighs]

30:15.606 --> 30:18.359
[Patton] Look at that brick wall.
Louis is gonna shit.

30:18.443 --> 30:21.154
Welcome to our first annual
neighborhood block party

30:21.237 --> 30:25.074
and Open Arms, open carry,
guns-for-everyone benefit.

30:25.158 --> 30:27.327
-[gunshot]
-Oh, God! Okay.

30:27.410 --> 30:29.620
I just think we could clap instead--

30:29.704 --> 30:30.913
-[gunshots]
-Oh, God! Okay.

30:30.997 --> 30:32.040
-[cheering]
-There's no need--

30:32.123 --> 30:33.124
-[gunshot]
-[Maria] Oh!

30:33.207 --> 30:35.251
The point is, I am not doing comedy.

30:35.335 --> 30:39.297
I am trying to bring people together
because you mean so much to me.

30:39.380 --> 30:42.383
And, I really want to be a part
of this community,

30:42.467 --> 30:44.844
-I love... I love you.
-[guns cocking]

30:46.137 --> 30:47.263
Be funnier!

30:47.347 --> 30:50.266
-You should try to be funnier.
-[whispering] Okay.

30:50.350 --> 30:52.226
Okay. Uh...

30:52.310 --> 30:54.979
-You guys thinking of shooting her?
-It's come up.

30:55.063 --> 30:56.731
We're kicking it around.

30:56.814 --> 30:58.524
A while back, I made a vision board.

30:58.608 --> 31:04.072
To manifest my need for community,
I cut out a picture of a park bench

31:04.155 --> 31:05.406
and I pasted that on there.

31:05.490 --> 31:07.116
Fuck this fuck bench!

31:07.200 --> 31:09.619
You're doing great! [laughing]

31:09.702 --> 31:12.455
What time is it?
That's my eight hours.

31:12.538 --> 31:15.041
Okay, that's Oscar. [chuckling]

31:15.124 --> 31:17.710
He's one of the wonderful, angry...

31:18.336 --> 31:21.589
angry, wonderful people
in our neighborhood.

31:21.672 --> 31:22.965
What should I do, Patton?

31:23.049 --> 31:24.425
-Hands off the mic.
-Okay.

31:24.509 --> 31:27.053
[inhaling]
Ladies and gentlemen, Patton Oswalt!

31:27.136 --> 31:28.262
He can do comedy!

31:28.346 --> 31:29.722
[cheering]

31:29.806 --> 31:32.767
-[crowd whooping]
-Because it's not his show!

31:32.850 --> 31:34.977
[Mark] Thanks a lot.

31:35.061 --> 31:36.562
-Hey, guys.
-[gunshot]

31:36.646 --> 31:39.857
Well, I know a lot of you guys
are pissed off.

31:39.941 --> 31:42.110
I've been pissed off all day, you know?

31:42.193 --> 31:44.737
And here's the thing
about being pissed off

31:44.821 --> 31:47.240
is if you're really pissed off,

31:47.323 --> 31:49.367
the joke's probably on you.

31:49.450 --> 31:51.119
[all laughing]

31:53.037 --> 31:56.332
Oh, honey, wake up, wake up.

31:56.416 --> 31:58.584
[sighs] Your purple van's almost here.

31:58.668 --> 32:00.378
No, they're not coming.

32:00.461 --> 32:02.380
They're never coming again.

32:02.463 --> 32:04.090
Not after badminton.

32:05.425 --> 32:07.718
[Patton] <i>It doesn't matter</i>
<i>if you piss people off,</i>

32:07.802 --> 32:10.721
<i>what matters is the people</i>
<i>who show up after that.</i>

32:10.805 --> 32:13.516
-[gasps]
<i>-Those are the people to hang on to.</i>

32:14.559 --> 32:16.185
They're here.

32:18.062 --> 32:20.440
I need my backpack!

32:24.152 --> 32:26.195
[Patton] <i>Real friends</i>
<i>are there for you.</i>

32:26.279 --> 32:27.822
<i>And you're there for them.</i>

32:27.905 --> 32:29.949
With the exception of my friend Maria,

32:30.032 --> 32:33.202
who I don't know how much longer
I'm gonna be there for.

32:33.286 --> 32:35.079
-Guys, look...
-[Maria chuckles]

32:35.163 --> 32:38.332
So it looks like love isn't gonna find me
anytime soon.

32:38.416 --> 32:40.585
Or friendship and community.

32:40.668 --> 32:43.337
But you know what?
I'm on a journey.

32:43.421 --> 32:46.507
My show seems like
it's really finding its own voice.

32:46.591 --> 32:48.092
Hey, apropos of nothing,

32:48.176 --> 32:51.095
do you guys love or hate
the term "gun nuts"?

32:51.179 --> 32:52.472
-[bullet ricocheting]
-Okay.

32:53.431 --> 32:56.434
It's Patton's voice.
But he is very good.

32:56.517 --> 32:59.687
...express how you feel,
whether it's good or bad.

32:59.770 --> 33:04.066
And do not let people force you
to do what you don't wanna do!

33:04.150 --> 33:05.610
[woman] Like this bench!

33:05.693 --> 33:09.697
Yes, there you go! Thank you!
Don't get pissed off at each other.

33:09.780 --> 33:11.073
Get pissed off at the bench.

33:11.157 --> 33:13.659
-[all cheering]
-[woman] That's right!

33:13.743 --> 33:15.703
[man] Take down this wooden abortion.

33:15.786 --> 33:16.954
-Yeah!
-Come on!

33:17.038 --> 33:18.289
Whoo!

33:20.291 --> 33:21.417
[Maria] My bench!

33:21.501 --> 33:24.045
It's bringing people together!

33:24.128 --> 33:26.881
Vision board! [laughing]

33:29.342 --> 33:31.511
Boom! Manifested.

33:32.094 --> 33:34.138
<i> ♪ I don't know what I'm doing ♪</i>

33:34.222 --> 33:35.681
[Maria] Yeah!

33:37.767 --> 33:40.478
<i>♪ More than half of the time ♪</i>

33:40.561 --> 33:42.730
[laughing] Good job.

